parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the airbag system can lead to unexpected deployments, failure to deploy in the event of an accident, or false warnings, which can cause physical harm, emotional distress, and compromise vehicle safety.
symptoms: airbag fails to deploy in an accident
airbag warning light flashes on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause fires, stalling, and damage to vehicle components, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: the electrical harness blows a fuse
the radio light is burned out
the trunk light or hood light is not working

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall, not start, or catch on fire, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
The failure of the fuse system can cause electrical overloads, fires, and damage to vehicle components, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: the electrical harness keeps blowing a fuse
no fuse trips to stop the short circuit.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause the vehicle to accelerate out of control, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities. This issue can also lead to loss of control, fishtailing, and damage to property.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly and unexpectedly
reaching high speeds (up to 70 mph) and making it difficult or impossible to control the vehicle. The vehicle may also surge to high RPMs during idling.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Clutch Failure Due to Plastic Bushing
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The use of a plastic bushing in the clutch system can cause the clutch to fail, leading to difficulty shifting gears, stalling, and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The engine revs at a high rate
the transmission gears do not engage properly
and the clutch pedal feels soft or spongy.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Intermittent stalling can cause the vehicle to lose power and stall, potentially leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: especially when making turns or at idle or near idle speeds
and the airbag light may blink on and off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine malfunction can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, or even catch fire, potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The engine races or revs at a high rate
and there may be a strong scent of oil burning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: EGR valve malfunction can cause the engine to run poorly, leading to decreased performance and potentially causing the vehicle to stall.
symptoms: The EGR valve may need to be replaced due to malfunction.
